                            <comment id="12925085" author="nspiegelberg" created="Tue, 26 Oct 2010 18:47:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Code prior to this patch is probably not sorted right, so the fix I give won&apos;t be backwards compatible for correctly finding meta data without further effort.  The worst case should be that you request a meta block and it isn&apos;t found.  In our case, this is fine because all we store in META is bloom data.  Note that this bug was introduced by the addition of BloomFilters, so only 0.89 + 0.90 users will experience any migration &apos;oddities&apos;, 0.20 users who upgrade should be fine.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12925369" author="stack" created="Wed, 27 Oct 2010 13:45:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Nicolas. Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
